# Senior Review Workflow

When asked to review code, use this structure:

## Summary

Briefly state the overall quality and risk level.

## Critical Issues

Use priority labels:

- P0: security/data loss/build broken
- P1: serious production risk
- P2: maintainability or correctness issue
- P3: cleanup

For each issue include:

- Problem
- Why it matters
- File or area
- Suggested fix

## Architecture Review

Check:

- Separation of concerns
- Dependency direction
- DTO/entity boundaries
- Error handling
- Auth flow
- Database consistency

## Security Review

Check:

- Authentication
- Authorization
- Secrets
- Input validation
- CORS/CSRF
- Token handling
- Sensitive logging

## Testing Review

Check:

- Missing tests
- Weak tests
- Edge cases
- Integration coverage

## Final Verdict

Use one of:

- Ready to merge
- Merge after minor fixes
- Needs serious fixes
- Do not merge
